text: Yew Tee MRT station (NS5) is an above-ground Mass Rapid Transit (MRT) station on the North South Line in Choa Chu Kang, Singapore. ==History== The station was built in 1995, along with the five other stations of the North South Line Woodlands Extension. The two-storey station building, with a simple design and a kampung-style roof, was officially opened on 10 February 1996. The construction of the station affected 16 factories as land between the Yew Tee and Kranji MRT stations was bought by the government. The station was called Choa Chu Kang North. It was renamed Yew Tee in 1994. ==Related pages== *Mass Rapid Transit (Singapore) == References == ==Other websites== * Category:Mass Rapid Transit (Singapore) stations Category:1996 establishments in Asia Category:20th-century establishments in Singapore
